WEBVTT

00:00:02.819 --> 00:00:06.620
Welcome to another edition of JW Broadcasting.

00:00:06.620 --> 00:00:08.939
Here are this month's highlights.

00:00:08.939 --> 00:00:10.820
What is it like to engage in the special

00:00:10.820 --> 00:00:13.140
metropolitan witnessing work in the bustling

00:00:13.140 --> 00:00:16.339
United States city of San Francisco?

00:00:16.339 --> 00:00:18.059
We'll hear encouraging experiences

00:00:18.059 --> 00:00:19.980
from brothers and sisters who preach

00:00:19.980 --> 00:00:21.859
in this diverse language field.

00:00:22.780 --> 00:00:25.460
And young ones serve Jehovah successfully,

00:00:25.460 --> 00:00:29.059
even if their family spiritual activity stops.

00:00:29.059 --> 00:00:31.699
We'll hear from a sister who tells what kept her love

00:00:31.699 --> 00:00:34.060
for Jehovah growing, brought her family's

00:00:34.060 --> 00:00:37.979
busy show business career, and we'll discuss

00:00:37.979 --> 00:00:41.060
the beautiful quality of loyalty,

00:00:41.060 --> 00:00:43.259
including an interview with a couple

00:00:43.259 --> 00:00:47.460
who has served Jehovah loyally for over 60 years.

00:00:47.460 --> 00:01:11.780
All ahead, I'm JW Broadcasting for August 2016.

00:01:12.060 --> 00:01:15.019
This month's theme is taken from David's poetic song

00:01:15.019 --> 00:01:19.019
to Jehovah at Psalm 1825, which states,

00:01:19.060 --> 00:01:23.019
with someone loyal, you act in loyalty.

00:01:23.019 --> 00:01:25.939
The Hebrew term act in loyalty reminds us

00:01:25.939 --> 00:01:29.060
of God's loyal love that is love motivated

00:01:29.060 --> 00:01:34.060
by commitment, integrity, loyalty, and deep attachment.

00:01:34.540 --> 00:01:37.579
So loyalty is more than just a feeling.

00:01:37.579 --> 00:01:40.620
It is active, it's rooted in love.

00:01:40.620 --> 00:01:42.939
How comforting it is to know that Jehovah

00:01:42.939 --> 00:01:46.859
lovingly attaches himself to those who are loyal to him.

00:01:47.819 --> 00:01:51.459
What motivated David to write the words at Psalm 1825?

00:01:52.379 --> 00:01:54.980
The superscription reveals that it was composed

00:01:54.980 --> 00:01:58.939
after Jehovah rescued him from the hand of all his enemies

00:01:58.939 --> 00:02:00.500
and from the hand of Saul.

00:02:01.579 --> 00:02:04.659
Think of the great joy and relief he must have felt

00:02:04.659 --> 00:02:07.739
after experiencing firsthand Jehovah's loyal love

00:02:07.739 --> 00:02:09.539
and mighty saving acts.

00:02:10.460 --> 00:02:13.620
However, throughout his life, David experienced

00:02:13.740 --> 00:02:16.500
disloyalty at its worst.

00:02:16.500 --> 00:02:20.060
From his king Saul, from his wife Michael,

00:02:20.060 --> 00:02:22.620
from his trusted counselor, Ahithofel,

00:02:22.620 --> 00:02:25.139
and from his son, Absalom.

00:02:25.139 --> 00:02:26.900
He felt the deep hurt of betrayal

00:02:26.900 --> 00:02:29.099
by those he trusted and loved most.

00:02:30.340 --> 00:02:32.979
Loyalty is a choice.

00:02:32.979 --> 00:02:36.460
What do we find when we look back at David's life?

00:02:36.460 --> 00:02:40.419
David chose to stay loyal to God.

00:02:40.419 --> 00:02:43.259
From a humble shepherd boy carrying for his sheep

00:02:43.259 --> 00:02:46.139
to a valiant king carrying for the nation,

00:02:46.139 --> 00:02:48.740
he proved to be someone loyal,

00:02:48.740 --> 00:02:50.740
a man agreeable to Jehovah's heart.

00:02:52.180 --> 00:02:55.180
But it can be a real test to maintain loyalty to God

00:02:55.180 --> 00:02:56.780
when we face injustices.

00:02:57.780 --> 00:03:00.300
Imagine the desperate situation that David

00:03:00.300 --> 00:03:02.180
and his mighty warriors experienced

00:03:02.180 --> 00:03:05.780
when they were fugitives, forced to hide in the wilderness,

00:03:05.780 --> 00:03:08.060
often low on provisions.

00:03:08.060 --> 00:03:11.139
They saw firsthand King Saul's jealous rage.

00:03:12.139 --> 00:03:13.939
But what choice did David make

00:03:13.939 --> 00:03:16.780
when urged by his men to seize the opportunity

00:03:16.780 --> 00:03:18.099
to take Saul's life?

00:03:19.139 --> 00:03:24.300
Notice what David told his men at first Samuel 24 and verse six.

00:03:25.740 --> 00:03:28.219
It is unthinkable from Jehovah's standpoint

00:03:28.219 --> 00:03:30.780
that I should do such a thing to my Lord,

00:03:30.780 --> 00:03:32.659
the anointed of Jehovah,

00:03:32.659 --> 00:03:34.699
by lifting my hand against him

00:03:34.699 --> 00:03:38.099
for he is the anointed of Jehovah.

00:03:39.099 --> 00:03:42.099
David knew that if he remained loyal,

00:03:42.099 --> 00:03:44.740
Jehovah would remain loyal to him.

00:03:44.740 --> 00:03:47.099
He would show him loyal love.

00:03:47.099 --> 00:03:49.460
He humbly put aside his personal feelings

00:03:49.460 --> 00:03:52.620
and viewed matters from Jehovah's perspective.

00:03:52.620 --> 00:03:57.139
He chose to wait patiently for Jehovah to act in loyalty.

00:03:58.060 --> 00:04:00.580
We'll soon be facing life-changing events

00:04:00.580 --> 00:04:02.099
for told in the Bible

00:04:02.099 --> 00:04:06.780
that will test our loyalty to Jehovah and his organization.

00:04:06.939 --> 00:04:09.900
So now is the time to strengthen our loyalty.

00:04:10.699 --> 00:04:13.259
As we do, we can be sure that Jehovah

00:04:13.259 --> 00:04:15.259
knows our circumstances,

00:04:15.259 --> 00:04:18.100
perhaps injustices we have experienced

00:04:18.100 --> 00:04:20.740
and will reward our loyal service.

00:04:21.699 --> 00:04:23.300
So ask yourself,

00:04:23.300 --> 00:04:28.300
what loyal actions will motivate Jehovah to be loyal to me?

00:04:28.420 --> 00:04:30.060
Let's consider three areas.

00:04:30.939 --> 00:04:35.259
First, we can be loyal to Jehovah by defending him.

00:04:36.100 --> 00:04:38.500
But Jehovah is a sovereign of the universe.

00:04:38.500 --> 00:04:40.300
How can we come to his defense?

00:04:41.180 --> 00:04:45.459
We can learn how from the fine example of a lie-hoo.

00:04:45.459 --> 00:04:48.139
In the book of Job, a lie-hoo listened patiently

00:04:48.139 --> 00:04:51.139
as Job and his three false confidors spoke.

00:04:51.139 --> 00:04:56.139
Notice a lie-hoo's reaction at Job 32 versus 2 and 3.

00:04:57.740 --> 00:04:59.699
His anger blazed against Job

00:04:59.699 --> 00:05:03.740
for trying to prove himself right rather than God.

00:05:03.779 --> 00:05:06.740
He was also very angry with Job's three companions

00:05:06.740 --> 00:05:09.300
because they could not find an answer

00:05:09.300 --> 00:05:12.139
but had declared God wicked.

00:05:13.300 --> 00:05:14.899
A fire of righteous indignation

00:05:14.899 --> 00:05:17.500
was burning inside young a lie-hoo.

00:05:17.500 --> 00:05:20.939
In Job 36 versus 2 and 3,

00:05:20.939 --> 00:05:24.699
he lorally comes to Jehovah's defense saying,

00:05:24.699 --> 00:05:28.420
be patient with me a little longer while I explain

00:05:28.420 --> 00:05:31.860
for I still have words to speak on God's behalf.

00:05:31.899 --> 00:05:35.180
I will speak comprehensively about what I know

00:05:35.180 --> 00:05:39.180
and I will ascribe righteousness to my maker.

00:05:39.180 --> 00:05:42.579
A lie-hoo courageously proved loyal by praising

00:05:42.579 --> 00:05:44.939
and yes, defending God.

00:05:46.420 --> 00:05:49.980
Why do we need to come to Jehovah's defense today?

00:05:49.980 --> 00:05:52.339
Because our loving Heavenly Father is blasphemed

00:05:52.339 --> 00:05:55.300
in so many ways, false religions claim

00:05:55.300 --> 00:05:56.899
that he's part of a Trinity

00:05:56.899 --> 00:05:59.939
and that he torments people eternally in burning hell.

00:06:00.779 --> 00:06:02.819
Others say that he does not exist

00:06:02.819 --> 00:06:06.339
or if he does, he doesn't really care about us.

00:06:06.339 --> 00:06:09.300
We know that such lies come from Satan the devil.

00:06:10.459 --> 00:06:13.019
We demonstrate our loyalty by speaking

00:06:13.019 --> 00:06:15.220
in defense of Jehovah,

00:06:15.220 --> 00:06:18.379
thereby proving Satan the liar that he is.

00:06:18.379 --> 00:06:20.819
We boldly and zealously proclaim

00:06:20.819 --> 00:06:23.740
that he does exist as the Almighty God

00:06:23.740 --> 00:06:27.139
and that he is wise, just and loving

00:06:27.139 --> 00:06:29.860
and that he will soon bring an end to all evil

00:06:29.860 --> 00:06:32.500
and reward his loyal ones with eternal life.

00:06:33.459 --> 00:06:36.379
Jehovah could make the stones cry out in defense,

00:06:36.379 --> 00:06:39.300
yet he honors his loyal witnesses,

00:06:39.300 --> 00:06:41.980
you and me with this fine privilege.

00:06:43.259 --> 00:06:46.060
Second, we can be loyal to Jehovah

00:06:46.060 --> 00:06:49.220
by being loyal to the faithful and discreet slave,

00:06:49.220 --> 00:06:50.300
the governing body.

00:06:51.220 --> 00:06:53.379
Jehovah and Jesus are using the faithful

00:06:53.379 --> 00:06:55.899
and discreet slave to feed us spiritually.

00:06:55.899 --> 00:06:59.620
So we owe our loyalty to that slave.

00:06:59.620 --> 00:07:02.100
But some may say, isn't the governing body

00:07:02.100 --> 00:07:04.379
made up of imperfect men?

00:07:04.379 --> 00:07:06.180
Yes, it is.

00:07:06.180 --> 00:07:09.259
The last perfect person to walk the earth was Jesus himself.

00:07:10.180 --> 00:07:14.740
There is no perfect person or organization on the globe.

00:07:14.740 --> 00:07:17.259
But as a long time faithful brother used to say,

00:07:17.259 --> 00:07:20.379
this is the best imperfect organization on earth.

00:07:21.300 --> 00:07:24.139
Jesus didn't say the slave would be infallible.

00:07:24.139 --> 00:07:28.259
He said it would be faithful and discreet.

00:07:28.259 --> 00:07:31.220
The way we listen to and obey the faithful slave

00:07:31.220 --> 00:07:34.459
has a direct bearing on the strength of our friendship

00:07:34.459 --> 00:07:35.860
with God.

00:07:35.860 --> 00:07:40.660
In fact, it means our very life.

00:07:40.660 --> 00:07:43.459
But what if the governing body serves some spiritual food

00:07:43.459 --> 00:07:45.259
that is not to our liking?

00:07:45.259 --> 00:07:49.060
Or what if we do not fully understand or agree

00:07:49.060 --> 00:07:51.500
with a clarification of a belief?

00:07:52.379 --> 00:07:54.579
On one occasion, Jesus followers,

00:07:54.579 --> 00:07:58.100
including the Apostle Peter, were confronted with a new teaching.

00:07:58.899 --> 00:08:01.019
How did most react?

00:08:01.019 --> 00:08:04.060
Notice John 6 and verse 60.

00:08:04.060 --> 00:08:06.980
It states, when they heard this,

00:08:06.980 --> 00:08:08.699
many of his disciples said,

00:08:08.699 --> 00:08:10.339
this speech is shocking.

00:08:10.339 --> 00:08:12.300
Who can listen to it?

00:08:12.300 --> 00:08:13.560
The result?

00:08:13.560 --> 00:08:17.459
Continuing in verse 66, because of this,

00:08:17.459 --> 00:08:20.620
many of his disciples went off to the things behind

00:08:20.620 --> 00:08:22.420
and would no longer walk with him.

00:08:23.540 --> 00:08:27.420
But how did Peter respond when Jesus asked them,

00:08:27.420 --> 00:08:29.339
are you too stumbled?

00:08:29.339 --> 00:08:32.100
At John 6, 68, we read,

00:08:32.100 --> 00:08:34.139
Simon Peter answered him,

00:08:34.139 --> 00:08:37.019
Lord, whom shall we go away to?

00:08:37.019 --> 00:08:39.779
You have sayings of everlasting life.

00:08:41.100 --> 00:08:43.100
What loyalty?

00:08:43.100 --> 00:08:45.820
Peter's loyalty was based on solid evidence

00:08:45.820 --> 00:08:48.539
that Jesus was the Messiah.

00:08:48.539 --> 00:08:51.779
His loyalty was evidence of his faith.

00:08:51.779 --> 00:08:55.779
That is the kind of loyalty we want to imitate today.

00:08:56.779 --> 00:09:00.779
There are times we must wait on Jehovah to clarify matters.

00:09:00.779 --> 00:09:05.580
In the meantime, may we prove ourselves loyal, like Peter,

00:09:05.580 --> 00:09:08.779
and follow closely the lead of the faithful slave,

00:09:08.779 --> 00:09:13.379
who closely follow in the footsteps of their master, Jesus.

00:09:14.379 --> 00:09:18.379
At times, though, we receive counsel that touches us personally.

00:09:18.379 --> 00:09:20.779
For instance, on JW Broadcasting,

00:09:20.779 --> 00:09:23.980
we receive loving reminders from members of the governing body

00:09:24.179 --> 00:09:26.100
to be forgiving,

00:09:26.100 --> 00:09:28.620
to honor Jehovah with our valuable things,

00:09:28.620 --> 00:09:31.820
and to remain spiritually alert.

00:09:31.820 --> 00:09:34.299
Through the watchtower and at Christian meetings,

00:09:34.299 --> 00:09:37.299
we're reminded to be careful about our address and grooming,

00:09:37.299 --> 00:09:40.899
to choose good associates and wholesome entertainment,

00:09:40.899 --> 00:09:42.779
and to remain morally clean.

00:09:43.860 --> 00:09:46.940
Are we quick to respond and make needed adjustments?

00:09:46.940 --> 00:09:51.299
Or do we find ourselves wanting to defend our personal rights?

00:09:52.299 --> 00:09:56.019
A situation in the Apostle Paul's life tested his loyalty

00:09:56.019 --> 00:09:57.899
to theocratic direction?

00:09:57.899 --> 00:10:01.139
It's found in Acts chapter 21.

00:10:01.139 --> 00:10:04.740
As you recall, Paul arrived in Jerusalem in 56 CE

00:10:04.740 --> 00:10:07.419
after a very successful missionary tour.

00:10:07.419 --> 00:10:10.860
You can imagine his excitement as he related in detail

00:10:10.860 --> 00:10:14.700
that things God did among the nations through his ministry.

00:10:14.700 --> 00:10:17.860
After hearing Paul's extraordinary account,

00:10:17.980 --> 00:10:21.340
the older men revealed to Paul a problem in Judea

00:10:21.340 --> 00:10:24.220
that involved him personally.

00:10:24.220 --> 00:10:28.220
Read what they said at Acts 21 and verse 21.

00:10:29.620 --> 00:10:31.500
But they, the Jewish believers,

00:10:31.500 --> 00:10:33.139
have heard it rumored about you,

00:10:33.139 --> 00:10:36.179
that you have been teaching all the Jews among the nations

00:10:36.179 --> 00:10:39.340
in a apostasy from Moses,

00:10:39.340 --> 00:10:41.779
telling them not to circumcise their children,

00:10:41.779 --> 00:10:44.139
or to follow the customary practices.

00:10:45.139 --> 00:10:48.980
Well, perhaps Paul thought me in a apostate?

00:10:48.980 --> 00:10:49.820
Really?

00:10:49.820 --> 00:10:51.539
How can they say such a thing?

00:10:51.539 --> 00:10:53.980
I just finished my third missionary tour

00:10:53.980 --> 00:10:56.980
and look how Jehovah blessed the work.

00:10:56.980 --> 00:11:00.940
Nevertheless, the older men gave Paul very clear direction

00:11:00.940 --> 00:11:04.259
at Acts 21, verses 23 and 24,

00:11:04.259 --> 00:11:07.059
that he likely did not anticipate.

00:11:07.059 --> 00:11:07.980
And there it reads,

00:11:08.980 --> 00:11:10.659
so do what we tell you.

00:11:10.659 --> 00:11:14.019
We have four men who have put themselves under a vow.

00:11:14.019 --> 00:11:16.899
Take these men with you and cleanse yourself ceremonially

00:11:16.899 --> 00:11:19.700
together with them and take care of their expenses

00:11:19.700 --> 00:11:21.779
so that they may have their head shaved.

00:11:21.779 --> 00:11:24.019
Then everyone will know that there is nothing

00:11:24.019 --> 00:11:26.179
to the rumors they were told about you,

00:11:26.179 --> 00:11:28.620
but that you are walking orderly

00:11:28.620 --> 00:11:30.539
and you are also keeping the law.

00:11:31.580 --> 00:11:34.539
Was this the time for Paul to question their decision

00:11:34.539 --> 00:11:36.139
or demand his rights?

00:11:37.100 --> 00:11:38.860
He could have reason,

00:11:38.860 --> 00:11:40.740
didn't you read my letter to the Galatians

00:11:40.740 --> 00:11:43.340
where it says the law was nailed to the torture stake

00:11:43.379 --> 00:11:44.980
with Jesus?

00:11:44.980 --> 00:11:46.460
I did nothing wrong.

00:11:46.460 --> 00:11:48.860
Why do I have to put on this pretense

00:11:48.860 --> 00:11:51.899
just because a few are overly sensitive?

00:11:51.899 --> 00:11:55.379
No, he humbly did as they requested,

00:11:55.379 --> 00:11:57.340
although it nearly cost him his life.

00:11:58.340 --> 00:12:00.740
Yes, it meant swallowing his pride,

00:12:00.740 --> 00:12:03.220
but Paul knew there were bigger issues involved

00:12:03.220 --> 00:12:05.460
than his personal rights.

00:12:05.460 --> 00:12:09.340
He was considerate of the consciences of others.

00:12:09.340 --> 00:12:10.860
But more importantly,

00:12:10.860 --> 00:12:14.899
he showed his loyalty to Jehovah and to the governing body.

00:12:16.019 --> 00:12:18.820
Do we see the bigger issue in our life?

00:12:19.779 --> 00:12:23.620
Let us be determined to be humble, flexible,

00:12:23.620 --> 00:12:25.659
and obedient like Paul,

00:12:25.659 --> 00:12:28.700
and thereby prove ourselves faithful

00:12:28.700 --> 00:12:31.100
to the faithful and discrete slave.

00:12:32.740 --> 00:12:35.659
Third, we can be loyal to Jehovah

00:12:35.659 --> 00:12:38.019
by being loyal to the elders.

00:12:38.019 --> 00:12:40.500
We've discussed loyalty to Jehovah himself

00:12:40.500 --> 00:12:41.980
and to the faithful slave,

00:12:41.980 --> 00:12:43.940
but what about direction we receive

00:12:43.940 --> 00:12:47.220
from the elders in our congregation?

00:12:47.220 --> 00:12:49.700
We listen to our elders give talks and comments

00:12:49.700 --> 00:12:51.379
at the meetings each week.

00:12:51.379 --> 00:12:53.179
We work with them in the ministry

00:12:53.179 --> 00:12:55.340
and we associate with them.

00:12:55.340 --> 00:12:57.899
This regular contact gives us more opportunities

00:12:57.899 --> 00:13:01.100
to see their imperfections and flaws.

00:13:02.019 --> 00:13:05.299
We couldn't begin to focus on their weaknesses,

00:13:05.299 --> 00:13:07.700
weakening our trust in God's arrangement.

00:13:08.620 --> 00:13:12.299
For example, if you zoom in on any of our pictures

00:13:12.299 --> 00:13:13.740
in our magazines,

00:13:13.740 --> 00:13:17.220
all you'll see are colored spots or pixels.

00:13:17.220 --> 00:13:19.019
But when you zoom out,

00:13:19.019 --> 00:13:21.659
you see a beautiful photo or painting.

00:13:22.700 --> 00:13:25.379
Similarly, when looking at our elders,

00:13:25.379 --> 00:13:27.700
don't zoom in on their imperfections,

00:13:27.700 --> 00:13:29.059
the spots of ink,

00:13:29.059 --> 00:13:31.539
rather see the big picture.

00:13:33.059 --> 00:13:35.940
Why then is it so important to strengthen our loyalty

00:13:35.940 --> 00:13:38.419
to our hardworking, loving shepherds?

00:13:38.419 --> 00:13:40.299
Because these gifts and men

00:13:40.299 --> 00:13:43.419
aren't expression of Jehovah's loyal love

00:13:43.419 --> 00:13:46.100
as they loyalty lead, feed,

00:13:46.100 --> 00:13:48.860
and protect his precious sheep.

00:13:48.860 --> 00:13:50.419
As the great tribulation nears,

00:13:50.419 --> 00:13:51.820
our survival will depend

00:13:51.820 --> 00:13:54.580
and our readiness to respond to their direction

00:13:54.580 --> 00:13:57.139
as they follow the governing body's direction.

00:13:58.220 --> 00:14:00.580
Our loyalty is not to men,

00:14:00.580 --> 00:14:03.820
but to Jehovah's arrangement made up of imperfect,

00:14:03.820 --> 00:14:04.940
but loyal men.

00:14:05.899 --> 00:14:07.779
That is a lesson that Korah,

00:14:07.779 --> 00:14:11.620
Nathan, and a Byron refuse to learn.

00:14:11.620 --> 00:14:13.000
In this clip from the video

00:14:13.000 --> 00:14:14.899
Respect Jehovah's Authority,

00:14:14.899 --> 00:14:18.100
listen to Korah's defiant attitude toward Moses

00:14:18.100 --> 00:14:20.740
as taken from Numbers chapter 16.

00:14:28.470 --> 00:14:29.990
That is enough of you

00:14:31.070 --> 00:14:34.830
because the whole assembly are all of them holy

00:14:34.830 --> 00:14:37.070
and Jehovah's in their midst.

00:14:38.309 --> 00:14:40.470
Why then should you lift yourselves up

00:14:40.470 --> 00:14:42.909
above the congregation of Jehovah?

00:14:44.470 --> 00:14:47.029
Korah and the others made great pretenses

00:14:47.029 --> 00:14:48.590
of loyalty to God,

00:14:48.590 --> 00:14:50.950
but completely ignored the fact

00:14:50.950 --> 00:14:53.950
that Jehovah directly appointed Moses and Aaron.

00:14:55.629 --> 00:14:58.990
Who then were they really murmuring against?

