00:28:39.259 --> 00:28:43.339
they were listening to the radio long before TV, of course.

00:28:43.339 --> 00:28:47.619
And they heard a Jehovah's Witness give a talk.

00:28:47.619 --> 00:28:49.299
And then title of that talk was,

00:28:49.299 --> 00:28:50.819
where are the dead?

00:28:50.819 --> 00:28:51.700
Imagine.

00:28:51.700 --> 00:28:53.980
He gave all the scripture proof about the condition

00:28:53.980 --> 00:28:57.019
of the dead, the hope for the resurrection.

00:28:57.019 --> 00:29:01.140
And my father immediately said, this was the truth.

00:29:01.140 --> 00:29:04.180
So they wrote to the radio station,

00:29:04.180 --> 00:29:06.940
got a copy of the booklet of the talk.

00:29:06.940 --> 00:29:09.900
And then also they started receiving

00:29:09.900 --> 00:29:12.380
the subscription to the watch tower.

00:29:12.380 --> 00:29:15.380
But it wasn't until I was born and three years old

00:29:15.380 --> 00:29:18.099
that the witness was finally made contact with us.

00:29:18.099 --> 00:29:20.980
So what motivated you to make a choice

00:29:20.980 --> 00:29:22.819
to get into the full-time service

00:29:22.819 --> 00:29:24.940
and give your life to Jehovah?

00:29:24.940 --> 00:29:28.859
Well, what motivated me was when I attended a convention

00:29:28.859 --> 00:29:30.700
also in 56.

00:29:30.700 --> 00:29:32.859
I got baptized in 54.

00:29:32.859 --> 00:29:35.259
But in 56, I went to a district convention

00:29:35.259 --> 00:29:38.779
in Albany, California, and there was a pioneer booth.

00:29:38.779 --> 00:29:41.500
So I approached the booth and an older sister there

00:29:41.500 --> 00:29:44.059
looked at me and said, your young and strong,

00:29:44.059 --> 00:29:46.099
why aren't you a pioneer?

00:29:46.099 --> 00:29:48.740
I felt, well, yes, why not?

00:29:48.740 --> 00:29:51.380
So I started pioneering in 1956.

00:29:51.380 --> 00:29:52.539
That's what motivated me.

00:29:52.539 --> 00:29:54.619
And I was, really, I looked back at that.

00:29:54.619 --> 00:29:57.940
It was one of the best decisions I made in my life.

00:29:57.940 --> 00:29:59.619
Sandra, how about you?

00:29:59.619 --> 00:30:02.299
Motivating to put in a full-time service.

00:30:02.299 --> 00:30:05.859
Well, for a pioneer service, you know, it was like a given.

00:30:05.859 --> 00:30:08.500
Young people were just encouraged to pioneer.

00:30:08.500 --> 00:30:11.299
And most of the young people were doing that.

00:30:11.299 --> 00:30:13.460
You know, after a year or two, maybe they would get married

00:30:13.460 --> 00:30:16.380
and start a family, but those years and pioneering,

00:30:16.380 --> 00:30:18.339
starting out their life that way,

00:30:18.339 --> 00:30:21.700
gave them a wonderful basis for loyal service

00:30:21.700 --> 00:30:23.420
the rest of their life.

00:30:23.420 --> 00:30:24.539
Beautiful.

00:30:24.539 --> 00:30:26.299
So you were pioneering.

00:30:26.299 --> 00:30:29.140
How did your paths eventually meet?

00:30:29.140 --> 00:30:35.380
It was at a circuit assembly in Oakland, California, 1956.

00:30:35.380 --> 00:30:37.420
Very interesting things took place.

00:30:37.420 --> 00:30:40.819
I had the job of dismantling the stage.

00:30:40.819 --> 00:30:44.099
And I was carrying this large piece of plywood off the stage

00:30:44.099 --> 00:30:47.339
and I ran right into Sandra and knocked her flat.

00:30:47.339 --> 00:30:49.380
Well, I took advantage of the opportunity.

00:30:49.380 --> 00:30:52.779
I thought, well, that's not the best way to introduce yourself.

00:30:52.779 --> 00:30:55.819
But I said, by the way, would you like to accompany me

00:30:55.819 --> 00:30:58.180
to a get-together some of the friends are having it?

00:30:58.180 --> 00:30:59.059
Very good, Bill.

00:30:59.059 --> 00:31:00.900
Well, yes, and I followed through on it.

00:31:00.900 --> 00:31:02.579
We had a lot of association.

00:31:02.579 --> 00:31:05.779
And after a number of months, we got married.

00:31:05.779 --> 00:31:07.299
And both of us were pioneering,

00:31:07.299 --> 00:31:09.779
very happy in our ministry serving Jehovah.

00:31:09.779 --> 00:31:12.220
You really swept her off her feet, literally.

00:31:12.220 --> 00:31:13.220
I fell for it.

00:31:13.220 --> 00:31:14.059
Very good.

00:31:14.059 --> 00:31:16.259
So shortly after you were married,

00:31:16.259 --> 00:31:18.579
I understand you received some direction.

00:31:18.579 --> 00:31:22.180
Yes, the circuit overseer visited our congregation.

00:31:22.180 --> 00:31:25.579
We were only married about a month, I think, when he came through.

00:31:25.579 --> 00:31:29.740
And he told us that the organization was looking for pioneers

00:31:29.740 --> 00:31:31.700
who'd be willing to serve as special pioneers

00:31:31.700 --> 00:31:33.740
and go wherever where the need was great

00:31:33.740 --> 00:31:36.420
in the United States, particularly.

00:31:36.420 --> 00:31:39.740
So we told them, sure, we'd be delighted to do it.

00:31:39.779 --> 00:31:42.140
And four months after our marriage,

00:31:42.140 --> 00:31:47.140
we received an assignment as special pioneers to Decora Ayua.

00:31:47.140 --> 00:31:49.460
Now, that was a very interesting place

00:31:49.460 --> 00:31:52.980
because there were only eight publishers in the congregation.

00:31:52.980 --> 00:31:56.140
But we arrived, started with the meetings there

00:31:56.140 --> 00:31:57.220
at the Kingdom Hall.

00:31:57.220 --> 00:31:59.980
And the Kingdom Hall was up above Hunts' variety store

00:31:59.980 --> 00:32:04.019
in downtown Decora, and we lived in a room behind it.

00:32:04.019 --> 00:32:06.099
Well, you know, you're on your own like that,

00:32:06.099 --> 00:32:07.940
not a lot of brothers around.

00:32:08.019 --> 00:32:10.140
So you look for encouragement and company,

00:32:10.140 --> 00:32:13.900
and we would travel down to Strawberry Point, Ayua

00:32:13.900 --> 00:32:16.980
to where Charles and Shirley Sonnetco lived

00:32:16.980 --> 00:32:19.859
in a log cabin, one room log cabin,

00:32:19.859 --> 00:32:21.579
and we'd go visit with them

00:32:21.579 --> 00:32:24.019
in order to have some mutual encouragement.

00:32:24.019 --> 00:32:26.220
It's a nice picture of you in that log cabin, too,

00:32:26.220 --> 00:32:27.940
as you were special pioneering.

00:32:27.940 --> 00:32:29.619
So you're busy in that work.

00:32:29.619 --> 00:32:32.380
What special invitation did you receive?

00:32:32.380 --> 00:32:35.779
Well, we received the invitation to attend Gillian,

00:32:35.779 --> 00:32:38.579
the 34th class of Gillian School,

00:32:38.579 --> 00:32:40.660
and that was a wonderful thing.

00:32:40.660 --> 00:32:42.420
After two and a half years of pioneering,

00:32:42.420 --> 00:32:44.299
special pioneering in Ayua,

00:32:44.299 --> 00:32:46.700
and we were assigned to Lebanon,

00:32:46.700 --> 00:32:48.779
but we were unable to enter Lebanon

00:32:48.779 --> 00:32:50.859
because we couldn't get the visa.

00:32:50.859 --> 00:32:52.740
So then the organization asked us,

00:32:52.740 --> 00:32:55.339
well, will you take an assignment to Morocco?

00:32:55.339 --> 00:32:56.859
We were ready to go anywhere.

00:32:56.859 --> 00:32:59.660
So that's how we took a boat from New York City,

00:32:59.660 --> 00:33:02.980
five days across the Atlantic to Casablanca.

00:33:02.980 --> 00:33:03.819
Well, very nice.

00:33:03.819 --> 00:33:07.940
What was it like to be in the missionary service in Morocco?

00:33:07.940 --> 00:33:09.339
It was very interesting.

00:33:09.339 --> 00:33:13.059
We really enjoyed it, but you know, we only spoke English.

00:33:13.059 --> 00:33:16.180
So in Morocco, we had to learn French,

00:33:16.180 --> 00:33:20.180
and the first month of our missionary service in Morocco

00:33:20.180 --> 00:33:24.700
was for 30 days you studied the language 11 hours a day.

00:33:24.700 --> 00:33:27.180
Well, that could get pretty tiring for 11 hours a day,

00:33:27.180 --> 00:33:28.700
so we'd go to the French movies

00:33:28.700 --> 00:33:31.019
and count that as language time.

00:33:31.019 --> 00:33:33.099
And then we were moved to Tangier,

00:33:33.140 --> 00:33:35.420
and there was a Spanish congregation in Tangier,

00:33:35.420 --> 00:33:38.539
and so we had to learn the Spanish language too.

00:33:38.539 --> 00:33:42.059
But that was really a rich blessing for the two of us

00:33:42.059 --> 00:33:44.019
to be exposed to that culture

00:33:44.019 --> 00:33:46.819
and to have that privilege of serving there.

00:33:46.819 --> 00:33:50.220
So after four years, I understand that you came back

00:33:50.220 --> 00:33:51.299
to visit your family.

00:33:51.299 --> 00:33:54.339
What events were challenging thereafter?

00:33:54.339 --> 00:33:56.859
I think Sandra can relate that.

00:33:56.859 --> 00:33:59.660
Well, it was usually permitted

00:33:59.660 --> 00:34:01.579
after you were in your assignment four years,

00:34:01.579 --> 00:34:02.859
but then you were allowed to come home

00:34:02.859 --> 00:34:05.819
at least to have a vacation, visit your family.

00:34:05.819 --> 00:34:08.099
But we got back, we visited our family,

00:34:08.099 --> 00:34:12.659
and while there, I had a medical examination

00:34:12.659 --> 00:34:15.179
and found out that I had a serious health problem.

00:34:15.179 --> 00:34:17.420
Of course, we didn't have the funds to cover that,

00:34:17.420 --> 00:34:19.739
so Bill wrote to the society,

00:34:19.739 --> 00:34:21.300
and we made arrangements.

00:34:21.300 --> 00:34:24.179
They said, well, just take care of your situation

00:34:24.179 --> 00:34:26.420
and let us know when you're free.

00:34:26.420 --> 00:34:30.139
So he got a job to take care of our medical needs

00:34:30.139 --> 00:34:32.780
as well as living conditions.

00:34:32.780 --> 00:34:36.099
But you know, we just felt like we were failures.

00:34:36.099 --> 00:34:37.739
Jehovah knew we were discouraged.

00:34:37.739 --> 00:34:40.380
He knew we felt distraught about this,

00:34:40.380 --> 00:34:44.139
so he knew just what we needed and he gave it to us.

00:34:44.139 --> 00:34:45.820
As I got to feeling better

00:34:45.820 --> 00:34:49.820
and we got more free in our use of time,

00:34:49.820 --> 00:34:53.900
we started pioneering and Jehovah blessed our ministry

00:34:53.900 --> 00:34:55.619
just incredibly.

00:34:55.619 --> 00:34:59.099
There were times in this supposedly

00:34:59.099 --> 00:35:02.380
unproductive territory that we had up to 25 people

00:35:02.380 --> 00:35:03.739
attending the meetings.

00:35:03.739 --> 00:35:05.300
Many of them got baptized

00:35:05.300 --> 00:35:07.380
and there are fast friends to this day.

00:35:07.380 --> 00:35:11.420
So Jehovah knows what you need and he provides it.

00:35:11.420 --> 00:35:13.659
That is beautiful.

00:35:13.659 --> 00:35:15.780
What temptation did you have to resist

00:35:15.780 --> 00:35:18.539
when you came back and going through these difficulties?

00:35:18.539 --> 00:35:20.500
Yeah, I think it's a temptation

00:35:20.500 --> 00:35:23.780
that confronts a lot of brothers and sisters

00:35:23.780 --> 00:35:25.980
who return because of health reasons.

00:35:26.980 --> 00:35:29.059
And some just end up settling down

00:35:29.059 --> 00:35:30.780
because of their circumstances.

00:35:30.780 --> 00:35:32.460
But the temptation there was,

00:35:32.460 --> 00:35:35.139
well, you're home, you've already done your service

00:35:35.139 --> 00:35:36.980
in Morocco for a number of years.

00:35:36.980 --> 00:35:38.340
You've been in the full-time ministry.

00:35:38.340 --> 00:35:41.659
Just settled down now via house.

00:35:41.659 --> 00:35:44.019
But really, that wasn't our desire.

00:35:44.019 --> 00:35:46.179
So as soon as Sandra got on her feet

00:35:46.179 --> 00:35:49.099
and was feeling well enough, we got pioneering.

00:35:49.099 --> 00:35:50.739
And then I wrote headquarters and I said,

00:35:50.739 --> 00:35:53.300
here we are, we're ready to take on whatever.

00:35:53.300 --> 00:35:54.980
What would you like us to do?

00:35:55.019 --> 00:35:56.860
Good example, thank you.

00:35:56.860 --> 00:35:59.579
So you made yourself available to the organization.

00:35:59.579 --> 00:36:01.500
Where did they send you next?

00:36:01.500 --> 00:36:02.900
A wonderful assignment.

00:36:02.900 --> 00:36:07.900
We were sent a special pioneers to Washington, DC

00:36:07.900 --> 00:36:11.420
to help start a Spanish congregation.

00:36:11.420 --> 00:36:14.739
And that was indeed a very rich blessing.

00:36:14.739 --> 00:36:17.019
We were there a year and a half

00:36:17.019 --> 00:36:21.420
until that little congregation was solid and was formed.

00:36:21.420 --> 00:36:23.699
And then we received another blessing.

00:36:23.699 --> 00:36:25.940
We pointed to the circuit work.

00:36:25.940 --> 00:36:28.579
So I had the Spanish circuit in Florida

00:36:28.579 --> 00:36:33.260
from Key West to Orlando, one circuit in the whole state.

00:36:33.260 --> 00:36:36.420
Then we came to New York City, lived in the Bronx.

00:36:36.420 --> 00:36:40.420
I had a circuit and we did district work in the Spanish field.

00:36:40.420 --> 00:36:43.460
Then to Texas, to what they call the Valley of Texas,

00:36:43.460 --> 00:36:46.860
the Rio Grande Valley for a couple of years on the circuit.

00:36:46.860 --> 00:36:49.219
And then the district in Spanish

00:36:49.219 --> 00:36:52.380
from Houston, Texas to Ube City, California.

00:36:52.420 --> 00:36:54.179
And we loved every minute of it.

00:36:54.179 --> 00:36:56.579
Well, that's definitely the traveling work.

00:36:56.579 --> 00:37:00.300
Then 1977 rolls around and you receive another invitation.

00:37:00.300 --> 00:37:01.380
Yes, indeed.

00:37:01.380 --> 00:37:04.659
We were doing pre-convention work in L.D.L.A.A.

00:37:04.659 --> 00:37:07.260
area at the Lermurt Assembly Hall.

00:37:07.260 --> 00:37:11.219
And we received a letter inviting us to come to Bethel.

00:37:11.219 --> 00:37:14.780
And that was a very, very special privilege

00:37:14.780 --> 00:37:16.380
to be invited to Bethel.

00:37:16.380 --> 00:37:17.980
I went into the service department

00:37:17.980 --> 00:37:19.460
because at that time, they invited

00:37:19.460 --> 00:37:21.659
a number of traveling overseers to come in

00:37:21.659 --> 00:37:23.739
and work in the service department.

00:37:23.739 --> 00:37:25.820
And Sandra went into housekeeping

00:37:25.820 --> 00:37:28.780
and we were both delighted to come to Bethel.

00:37:28.780 --> 00:37:31.099
Well, sort of.

00:37:31.099 --> 00:37:34.260
I really, I really loved the ministry.

00:37:34.260 --> 00:37:36.420
I loved the, especially there's a district

00:37:36.420 --> 00:37:38.539
working with the circuit overseer and his wife

00:37:38.539 --> 00:37:41.340
every week and out service.

00:37:41.340 --> 00:37:45.500
So I wasn't too anxious for this Bethel thing.

00:37:45.500 --> 00:37:49.500
But you know, to hope again, those what you need.

00:37:49.539 --> 00:37:53.659
We came here and we started adjusting to Bethel life.

00:37:53.659 --> 00:37:56.780
And it really proved out to be a real blessing

00:37:56.780 --> 00:37:59.900
because we got the close association

00:37:59.900 --> 00:38:03.260
with so many other loyal witnesses of Jehovah.

00:38:04.300 --> 00:38:06.380
Well, I'm sure you have many more experiences

00:38:06.380 --> 00:38:10.099
to let us know about, but we appreciate you sharing those.

00:38:10.099 --> 00:38:13.980
The governing body has made significant adjustments

00:38:13.980 --> 00:38:17.860
in the work that is taking place at Bethel and the field.

00:38:17.900 --> 00:38:21.099
And it has affected many long time faithful brothers,

00:38:21.099 --> 00:38:23.699
loyal brothers, and in the traveling work

00:38:23.699 --> 00:38:27.739
overseers in the congregation, overseers at Bethel.

00:38:27.739 --> 00:38:31.539
Bill, what do you think about some of these changes

00:38:31.539 --> 00:38:33.420
that the governing body has made recently?

00:38:33.420 --> 00:38:35.739
I think they're very wise decisions.

00:38:35.739 --> 00:38:37.860
They know what is needed.

00:38:37.860 --> 00:38:40.699
They appreciate the older men who have served for years.

00:38:40.699 --> 00:38:42.380
We know that the older brothers

00:38:42.380 --> 00:38:45.900
been in circuit work, district work, wherever.

00:38:45.900 --> 00:38:48.059
They're worthy of double honor because of the way

00:38:48.059 --> 00:38:50.619
they've given of themselves to the work.

00:38:50.619 --> 00:38:53.500
But we have to recognize to there comes a time

00:38:53.500 --> 00:38:56.900
when we want the younger men to come along

00:38:56.900 --> 00:38:58.699
to accept responsibility.

00:38:58.699 --> 00:39:01.059
And really, when we were young,

00:39:01.059 --> 00:39:05.059
we received responsibilities with very little background

00:39:05.059 --> 00:39:05.900
and training.

00:39:05.900 --> 00:39:08.940
Now we've got all these schools for kingdom evangelizers,

00:39:08.940 --> 00:39:11.940
the ministry's kingdom ministry school.

00:39:11.940 --> 00:39:14.820
So many opportunities for younger ones to be trained.

00:39:14.860 --> 00:39:17.940
And so I think it's a wonderful arrangement.

00:39:17.940 --> 00:39:21.139
Many thousands of young men are doing so well

00:39:21.139 --> 00:39:23.019
ready to accept responsibility.

00:39:23.019 --> 00:39:25.739
It's a blessing for the entire organization.

00:39:25.739 --> 00:39:27.219
Well, thank you for sharing that.

00:39:27.219 --> 00:39:29.380
That will benefit many brothers.

00:39:29.380 --> 00:39:31.739
So we look at this couple before us

00:39:31.739 --> 00:39:35.659
and we see someone who has made wise choices along the way.

00:39:35.659 --> 00:39:39.619
So we look back at over 60 years of faithful, loyal service.

00:39:39.619 --> 00:39:43.300
As you look back at decisions you were made in life,

00:39:43.380 --> 00:39:44.380
any regrets?

00:39:45.380 --> 00:39:46.940
Oh, absolutely none.

00:39:48.019 --> 00:39:52.739
We consider that whatever we have given up or done,

00:39:52.739 --> 00:39:55.139
it's been our gift to Jehovah.

00:39:55.139 --> 00:39:56.380
You know, when I was a little girl,

00:39:56.380 --> 00:39:58.219
I remember I used to go out on our farm

00:39:58.219 --> 00:40:01.300
and especially when there was a full moon.

00:40:01.300 --> 00:40:03.619
And I used to pray to Jehovah and I'd say,

00:40:04.980 --> 00:40:08.659
it just let me use up my life in your service.

00:40:08.659 --> 00:40:10.460
You know, he's answered that prayer

00:40:10.500 --> 00:40:13.579
because my life is majority of it used up

00:40:13.579 --> 00:40:15.860
and he's let me do it in his service.

00:40:15.860 --> 00:40:16.699
Beautiful.

00:40:16.699 --> 00:40:18.340
And Bill, how do you view sacrifices

00:40:18.340 --> 00:40:20.219
that you have made along the way?

00:40:20.219 --> 00:40:24.059
Well, as you know, a sacrifice can be something you give up

00:40:24.059 --> 00:40:25.980
to serve God perhaps,

00:40:25.980 --> 00:40:29.179
or a sacrifice can be what you give to Jehovah.

00:40:29.179 --> 00:40:31.019
Like David said in Psalm 54,

00:40:31.019 --> 00:40:33.860
I will sacrifice to you willingly.

00:40:33.860 --> 00:40:36.260
And that's how I view sacrifice.

00:40:37.219 --> 00:40:39.980
We're happy to give of ourselves to Jehovah God

00:40:39.980 --> 00:40:40.820
to serve Him.

00:40:40.820 --> 00:40:44.619
And I want to add to Sandra has been a wonderful partner

00:40:44.619 --> 00:40:46.380
with me, willing to go anywhere,

00:40:46.380 --> 00:40:49.780
put up with all kinds of circumstances and difficulty,

00:40:49.780 --> 00:40:52.780
a scripture that I, there are a number of good scriptures,

00:40:52.780 --> 00:40:54.139
obviously that we all love.

00:40:54.139 --> 00:40:56.940
But one in particular that stays in my mind

00:40:56.940 --> 00:41:00.619
is Romans chapter 14 verses seven and eight.

00:41:00.619 --> 00:41:03.820
We live, we live to Jehovah.

00:41:03.820 --> 00:41:06.860
We die, we die to Jehovah.

00:41:06.860 --> 00:41:09.059
So whether we live or we die,

00:41:09.059 --> 00:41:10.260
we belong to Jehovah.

00:41:10.260 --> 00:41:14.179
And we've made that decision, not just because he's the creator.

00:41:14.179 --> 00:41:18.420
We've made the decision to give ourselves to Jehovah God.

00:41:18.420 --> 00:41:22.619
So absolutely, we've had the best life possible.

00:41:22.619 --> 00:41:26.659
We have no regrets at all about what we've done

