00:42:00.340 --> 00:42:04.019
Sister Corey Wells explains how her family special talent

00:42:04.019 --> 00:42:11.949
almost kept her from riding on the road to life.

00:42:11.949 --> 00:42:14.630
The first rodeo I performed in front of an audience

00:42:14.630 --> 00:42:25.090
that was eight years old.

00:42:25.090 --> 00:42:29.849
We were considered one of the top two acts in rodeo,

00:42:29.849 --> 00:42:33.090
my strength lied in my fearlessness.

00:42:39.550 --> 00:42:43.269
Even though there was a certain amount of excitement,

00:42:43.269 --> 00:42:48.989
it was fun to travel, to be together as a family.

00:42:48.989 --> 00:42:55.250
It was empty.

00:42:55.250 --> 00:42:59.969
Trickriding is like gymnastics on the back of a running horse.

00:42:59.969 --> 00:43:02.050
We've had horses all of our life.

00:43:02.050 --> 00:43:06.929
My father specialized in training courses.

00:43:06.929 --> 00:43:13.360
He used to send us to the mountains riding all day long,

00:43:13.360 --> 00:43:15.039
and then we'd come home in the evening,

00:43:15.039 --> 00:43:17.880
and we would start trickriding.

00:43:17.880 --> 00:43:20.599
The way we learned was by a book.

00:43:20.599 --> 00:43:24.320
We looked at stick pictures that showed how it should be done,

00:43:24.320 --> 00:43:26.639
and so it was trial and error.

00:43:26.639 --> 00:43:30.679
At the same time that we were learning, our horses were learning.

00:43:30.679 --> 00:43:35.119
The horse that I rode just let me do anything.

00:43:35.119 --> 00:43:37.239
My horse's name was Sweetlips.

00:43:37.239 --> 00:43:41.400
I was eight when I got him, and I named him myself.

00:43:41.400 --> 00:43:44.360
He was like my best friend.

00:43:44.360 --> 00:43:48.440
My parents were very active in the rodeo as competitors.

00:43:48.440 --> 00:43:49.800
My mom was bell racing.

00:43:49.800 --> 00:43:53.360
My father was a saddle-brunk rider.

00:43:53.360 --> 00:43:56.679
I grew up as one of Jehovah's Witnesses,

00:43:56.679 --> 00:44:00.719
but when I was very young, maybe six or seven,

00:44:00.719 --> 00:44:03.719
my father stopped serving Jehovah.

00:44:03.719 --> 00:44:07.199
To be honest with you when they announced that at the Kingdom Hall,

00:44:07.199 --> 00:44:10.320
it really didn't have much meaning to me at the time.

00:44:10.320 --> 00:44:13.199
I didn't know what it meant.

00:44:13.199 --> 00:44:16.199
And I could see people crying, and so I cried,

00:44:16.199 --> 00:44:18.719
but I didn't really understand it.

00:44:18.719 --> 00:44:21.760
Really from that point, our family was not active

00:44:21.760 --> 00:44:24.599
as Jehovah's Witnesses.

00:44:24.599 --> 00:44:28.639
I grew up on the road traveling, rodeo to rodeo,

00:44:28.639 --> 00:44:33.039
from coast to coast, and from the south to the north,

00:44:33.039 --> 00:44:36.400
as far as the roads go.

00:44:36.400 --> 00:44:39.800
The four of us rode initially, Connie Kelly, myself,

00:44:39.800 --> 00:44:43.440
and my brother, Jim, our family traveled together.

00:44:43.440 --> 00:44:46.559
That meant a lot to me.

00:44:46.559 --> 00:44:49.679
What separated us from the others at the time

00:44:49.679 --> 00:44:53.280
was the high speed that we did it at.

00:44:53.280 --> 00:44:57.039
And also the difficulty with the tricks that we chose to do.

00:44:57.039 --> 00:44:58.639
People were very excited.

00:44:58.639 --> 00:45:03.599
They would hire us back at the same place year after year.

00:45:03.599 --> 00:45:08.639
Throughout all that time, we did not miss one memorial.

00:45:08.639 --> 00:45:09.719
We were always there.

00:45:09.719 --> 00:45:12.440
There was something in us.

00:45:12.440 --> 00:45:14.280
We didn't know it when we were little,

00:45:14.280 --> 00:45:19.519
but my parents had succeeded in planting the truth in our hearts.

00:45:19.519 --> 00:45:23.800
My link to the truth was my grandmother.

00:45:23.800 --> 00:45:26.159
I can remember going to the ranch and visiting her.

00:45:26.159 --> 00:45:27.400
She was very busy.

00:45:27.400 --> 00:45:30.360
But one thing that really sticks in my mind

00:45:30.360 --> 00:45:34.159
is she always studied every day.

00:45:34.159 --> 00:45:35.719
She read her Bible.

00:45:35.719 --> 00:45:38.000
Her magazines were studied.

00:45:38.000 --> 00:45:40.800
And I think it just put a seed in there

00:45:40.800 --> 00:45:44.400
that later on started to grow.

00:45:44.400 --> 00:45:48.039
I just felt like I needed direction.

00:45:48.039 --> 00:45:51.119
It's like a line was drawn in the sand.

00:45:51.119 --> 00:45:53.719
Take one path or the other.

00:45:53.719 --> 00:45:57.280
And so ironically, the first book that I picked up to read

00:45:57.280 --> 00:45:59.440
was the Bible.

00:45:59.440 --> 00:46:02.559
One of the scriptures that probably meant the most to me

00:46:02.559 --> 00:46:06.239
was Proverbs 35 and 6.

00:46:06.239 --> 00:46:08.360
Trust in Jehovah with all your heart

00:46:08.360 --> 00:46:11.119
and do not lean upon your own understanding.

00:46:11.119 --> 00:46:13.159
And all your ways, take notice of him.

00:46:13.159 --> 00:46:17.239
And he himself will make your path straight.

00:46:17.239 --> 00:46:19.440
I used to think about those words

00:46:19.440 --> 00:46:23.280
and what I would have to do to live up to them.

00:46:23.280 --> 00:46:26.239
Although we traveled with the rodeo about 10 months out

00:46:26.239 --> 00:46:29.400
of the year, we did go to the district convention

00:46:29.400 --> 00:46:32.440
and the live forever book came out.

00:46:32.440 --> 00:46:36.039
And there just came a time when I knew I

00:46:36.039 --> 00:46:38.440
needed to make changes.

00:46:38.440 --> 00:46:40.440
Sister started studying with me.

00:46:40.440 --> 00:46:43.000
And as I started reading the Bible for myself

00:46:43.000 --> 00:46:46.880
and studying, then Jehovah became real.

00:46:46.880 --> 00:46:50.239
All it took was one or two people in the whole family

00:46:50.239 --> 00:46:55.760
followed my father to return to the truth.

00:46:55.760 --> 00:46:57.920
Trick writing was our family business.

00:46:57.920 --> 00:46:59.400
It was our livelihood.

00:46:59.400 --> 00:47:01.719
But we had decided that we were done.

00:47:01.719 --> 00:47:03.559
We were going to stop.

00:47:03.559 --> 00:47:09.000
With that decision would come giving up everything we knew.

00:47:09.000 --> 00:47:12.079
I think the most difficult thing for me

00:47:12.079 --> 00:47:15.679
to do was to sell the horse.

00:47:15.679 --> 00:47:19.360
You just get such a close bond with them

00:47:19.360 --> 00:47:24.039
